Test Strategy
Bright has communicated with Opencart and has understood that we need to perform Functional Testing of all the functionalities mentioned in the above Scope section.

As part of Functional Testing,we will follow the below approach;

Step 1: Creation of Test Scenarios and Test Cases for the different features in scope.
-We will apply several Test Design Techniques while creating Test Cases such as Equivalence class partition,Decision Table testing,Use case Testing.
-We also use our expertise in Creating Test Cases by applying Error guessing, Exploratory Testing.

Step 2: Our testing process,when we get the application for Testing.
-Firstly,we will perform Smoke Testing to check if the different and important functionalities of the application are working.
-We reject the build,if the smoke Testing fails and will wait for the stable build before performing in depth testing of the application.
-Once we receive stable build which passes Smoke testing, We perform in depth testing using the Test cases created.
-We the report the bugs in bug tracking tool and send you the defect found on that day in a status of the email.
-As part of the Testing,we will perform the following types of Testing ; Smoke Testing and Sanity Testing,Regression Testing, Usability Testing and Functionality.
Step 3 : We will follow the below practices to make our Testing Better;
-Context Driven Testing : we will perform testing as per the context provided.
-Shift left Testing : we will start testing from the beginning of the development itself.
-Exploratory Testing: Using our expertise,we will perform exploratory testing.
-End to End flow Testing: we will Test end to end scenario which involves multiple functionalities.


Defect Reporting Procedure
The following will be noted;
-Any deviation from expected behaviour will be noted.
-Any usability issues will also be reported.
-After discovery of a defect,it will be retested to verify nature of the defect.
-All defects and Test cases will be recorded in an excelDocument.


